      <h2>üöÄ What We're Building</h2>
      <p>We're going to create a personal portfolio website - a webpage all about you! It will have:</p>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>‚úÖ Your name and photo</li>
        <li>‚úÖ Things you're good at (skills)</li>
        <li>‚úÖ Cool projects you've made</li>
        <li>‚úÖ How to contact you</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="lesson-card">
      <h2>üìù Step 1: Create a Folder</h2>
      <p>First, let's create a place to store your website files.</p>
      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">1</span>
          <div>
            <h4>Create a new folder on your computer</h4>
            <p>Name it <code>my-portfolio</code></p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">2</span>
          <div>
            <h4>Open that folder</h4>
            <p>Right-click inside and create a new text file</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">3</span>
          <div>
            <h4>Name it <code>index.html</code></h4>
            <p>Make sure it ends in .html not .txt!</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="lesson-card">
      <h2>üé® Step 2: Add Your Content</h2>
      <p>Now let's add content to your page. Copy this code:</p>
      
      <div class="code-block">
        <pre><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
  &lt;title&gt;My Portfolio&lt;/title&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
  &lt;h1&gt;Hi, I'm [Your Name]!&lt;/h1&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Welcome to my portfolio!&lt;/p&gt;
  
  &lt;h2&gt;About Me&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;[Write something about yourself]&lt;/p&gt;
  
  &lt;h2&gt;My Skills&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;ul&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Skill 1&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Skill 2&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;/ul&gt;
  
  &lt;h2&gt;Contact&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Email: your@email.com&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;</code></pre>
      </div>
      <p class="note">Replace [Your Name] and the other parts with your info!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="lesson-card">
      <h2>üéØ Step 3: View Your Website</h2>
      <p>Let's see what you made!</p>
      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">1</span>
          <div>
            <h4>Find your index.html file</h4>
            <p>Go to the folder where you saved it</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="step-num">2</span>
          <div>
            <h4>Double-click the file</h4>
            <p>It should open in your web browser!</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

